articles.description: Dimencio Vaughn scored 19 points with seven rebounds and three steals, Stevie Jordan scored 17 with six assists and Rider rolled past Siena 97-71 Thursday night to remain atop the Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference standings and extend its win streak...
articles.headline: Vaughn scores 19, Rider cruises past Siena 97-71 in MAAC

articles.description: Cortez Mitchell scored 17 points and Christian Keeling added 15 to lead Charleston Southern over Longwood 77-65 on Thursday night.
articles.headline: Charleston Southern pulls away to win 77-65

articles.description: Rokas Gustys piled up 22 points and 21 rebounds and Eli Pemberton scored 26 to propel Hofstra to a 90-84 victory over William & Mary on Thursday night.
articles.headline: Gustys, Pemberton spur Hofstra past William & Mary 90-84

articles.description: Oregon guard Payton Pritchard takes it all the way to the cup for the lay-in.
articles.headline: Oregon's Pritchard beats the USC defense for fast-break layup

articles.description: Dachon Burke drilled 4 of 5 from deep to score 27 points and Robert Morris used a borrowed gym to open its final homestand of the season, walloping Bryant 83-60 in a Northeast Conference battle at Duquesne University Thursday night.
articles.headline: Robert Morris borrows Duquesne arena, wallops Bryant, 83-60

articles.description: Reggie Dillard scored 21 points with three 3-pointers, JC Younger added 17 points with four 3s, and Presbyterian beat High Point 69-62 on Thursday night to end a three-game skid.
articles.headline: Dillard scores 21, Presbyterian downs High Point 69-62
